    <h1>Learning Resources for Block Code and Python</h1>
    <section class="resources_section" aria-labelledby="resources">
        <div class="resource_card" aria-labelledby="block-guides">
            <h2>Guides to Block Code</h2>
            <div class="grid-container">
                <div class="grid-item">
                    <a href="https://pencilcode.net/">Pencil Code</a>
                    <p>Pencil Code helps you learn coding by making fun projects like games and drawings. With simple tools and JavaScript, you can see your ideas come to life on the screen!</p>
                </div>
                <div class="grid-item">
                    <a href="https://scratch.mit.edu/">Scratch</a>
                    <p>Scratch lets you create games, stories, and animations by snapping together colorful coding blocks. It's an easy and fun way to learn the basics of programming, even if you're a beginner!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="resource_card" aria-labelledby="python-guides">
            <h2>Guides to Learning Python</h2>
            <div class="grid-container">
                <div class="grid-item">
                    <a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-programming-language-tutorial/">Geeks for Geeks</a>
                    <p>Geeks for Geeks offers a clear and easy guide to learning Python, with simple examples and explanations. It’s perfect for beginners who want to understand how Python works step by step.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="grid-item">
                    <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_intro.asp">w3schools</a>
                    <p>w3Schools gives a beginner-friendly introduction to Python, with interactive examples you can try right in your browser. It’s a great way to start learning Python at your own pace!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

